subSubSection.paragraph:
Similarly nestling diets of
Tachycineta bicolor (Vieillot, 1808 )
from Ottawa County (Michigan) were composed by Diptera: Brachycera ( 44.28 %), Diptera: Nematocera ( 12.5 %), Homoptera (12.0 %), Hymenoptera ( 14.5 %) and Coleoptera ( 7.6 %); the remainder of the diet ( 9.12 %) included Araneae , Hemiptera , Odonata, Ephemeroptera , Lepidoptera, Mollusca (clam and snail shells) and stones (
Johnson & Lombardo 2000
).
